Netology – Final Year Project (FYP)
Student: Jamie O’Neill – C22320301
Course: TU857/4
---
Netology is a web-based interactive elearning platform designed to help students learn computer networking through visual learning, gamification, and hands on practice.

The system includes a full frontend website, backend Flask API, user authentication, course pages, XP progression, and a custom built network sandbox where users can place routers, switches and PCs.

GitHub Repository
---
You can view the full project here:
https://github.com/JamieONeillTUD/Netology-FYP.git


How to Run the Project
---
1. Install required Python packages

Inside the backend folder, run:

pip install -r requirements.txt

2. Start the backend server

Run:

python app.py


You should see:

* Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000

3. Open the frontend

cmd and Rightclick on link in terminal

Project File Overview
---

- app.py
Main backend entry point, sets up Flask, configures CORS and registers routes.

- auth_routes.py
Handles user signup, login, logout, password hashing, and gets user account info from the database.

- course_routes.py
Provides all course related API routes including listing courses, fetching course details, tracking progress  and awarding XP.

- db.py
Creates and returns a connection to the PostgreSQL (AWS RDS) database for all backend queries.

- xp_system.py
Manages XP earnings and level progression, calculates new levels  and logs XP changes to the database.

- requirements.txt
Contains all Python dependencies needed to run the backend.

Frontend (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)
- index.html
Landing page that directs users to login or signup.

- login.html
User login page with email, password and validation.

- signup.html
Registration page that collects user details, skill level, and learning reasons.

- dashboard.html
Displays user info, XP, level, progress, and course lists (Continue, All, Completed).

- course.html
Displays a single course’s details, lessons, progress bar and XP reward.

- sandbox.html
Interactive networking sandbox where users can place routers/switches/PCs, drag devices, connect them and edit them.

- css/style.css
Custom styling for the entire frontend: colours, buttons, cards, layout, animations and theme.

- js/app.js
Frontend authentication logic for signup and login, form validation, and popup alerts.

- js/dashboard.js
Fetches user data and courses, displays progress, and handles dashboard UI interactions.

- js/course.js
Loads individual course info, lessons, progress bar, and handles lesson completion and XP updates.

- js/sandbox.js
Canvas based interactive network builder for placing, dragging, connecting and editing devices.